<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910315-0133</DOCNO><DOCID>910315-0133.</DOCID><HL>   McDonnell Douglas,   UAW Talks Are Said   To Be Progressing</HL><DATE>03/15/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   MD LABOR</CO><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)</IN><LP>   LONG BEACH, Calif. -- Negotiators for McDonnell DouglasCorp. and the United Auto Workers union report thatbargaining on a labor contract is &quot;progressing well,&quot; and avote on a new contract is expected to take place later thismonth.   The current accord, covering about 23,000 activerank-and-file members from four UAW locals, expires Sunday,and union members have given their leaders the authorizationto call a strike. But in a joint statement earlier this week,the company and the union said special meetings have beenscheduled for March 24, at which time a tentative contract isexpected to be presented to members for ratification.</LP><TEXT>   McDonnell Douglas and the UAW have been negotiating sinceFeb. 27.</TEXT></DOC>